The paper deals with lower bounds on the nonnegative ranks of matrices, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and linear algebra (cs.DS). The focus on approximation algorithms suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and optimization (cs.IT). The use of Razborov's rectangle corruption lemma and the mention of semidefinite programs suggest a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
